01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:43.000
you know, he, in the top tier of Gravity Theoris, points out that spinning black holes of that size

01:23:43.000 --> 01:23:48.000
do have time-like curves, where in principle you can, you know, cheat time by moving backwards and forwards,

01:23:48.000 --> 01:23:54.000
meeting previous and future versions of yourself in theory, in the best theory we have of black holes.

01:23:54.000 --> 01:24:00.000
So that's the, the nearest black hole of that size is going to be something like 500 light years away.

